Durban - A 31-year-old man has been arrested in connection with the murder of a missing one-year-old child who was found dead in Phoenix this week. According to KZN police, the man is expected to appear in the Verulam Magistrate’s Court on Monday. The infant was reported missing on Saturday after the child went missing from their home in the Amaoti area, north of Durban. On Wednesday night police found the decomposed body of the child in Trenance Manor, Phoenix. Police spokesperson, Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane said the man was arrested following an intelligence-driven operation. “Phoenix SAPS officers worked tirelessly following possible leads to locate a suspect involved in the murder of a child. “The officers were led to Eastern Cape, where the suspect was arrested and brought to SAPS Phoenix where he is being detained,” said Zwane. Zwane said a post mortem would be conducted to confirm the cause of death. POST